HEADWORD: Marinism
<hw>Ma*ri"nism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A bombastic
literary style marked by the use of metaphors and antitheses
characteristic of the Italian poet <person>Giambattista Marini</person>
(1569-1625).</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Ma*ri"nist</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
